@@ItemHTWidth
<TITLE ItemHTWidth function>
Summary
  Renders HTML-tagged contents using the specified Canvas, Rectangle, and Scaling factor.
Description
  ItemHTWidth is a function used to render the HTML-tagged contents using the specified in Text using
  the Canvas, Rectangle, State, and Scaling factor arguments. The return value is an Integer that
  indicates the width of the rendered Text.
  
  ItemHTWidth is used when rendering or auto-sizing the content in HTML-enabled controls like
  TJvHTLabel to determine the width of the rendered value.
  
  Use ItemHTHeight to determine the render height of HTML-tagged values.
  
  ItemHTWidth calls the HTMLTextWidth in JvJVCLUtils.pas.
Parameters
  Canvas - Canvas used to render the HTML content.
  Rect   - Rectangle to use for rendering HTML content.
  State  - Draw state values for the rendering operation.
  Text   - HTML tags to render.
  Scale  - Scaling factor for the render. Default value is 100.
Return value
  Integer - Width of the rendered HTML tag.
See Also
  HTMLTextWidth

